==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Lodestar
<hw>Lode"star`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr> }</mhw>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Load</ets>, <ets>lode</ets> + <ets>star.</ets>
See <er>Lode</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A star that leads; a guiding
star; esp., the polestar, Polaris; also, the constellation containing
the pole star, the cynosure (Ursa Minor).</def> <au>Chaucer.</au>
⟦ldquo⟧ Your eyes are <xex>lodestars</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The pilot can no <qex>loadstar</qex> see.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Something that serves as a guide or provides
direction; a cynosure{2}.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Something that attracts attention or on which the
atention is fixed; a cynosure{3}.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lodestone</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Loadstone</ent>⟦br⟧
